sub_title: Verpleegkundige in opleiding tot specialist, GGZ bij Fier
summary:
I am a  (psychiatric) nurse and a public health professional, with 12 years of experience in the international medical humanitarian field. I worked in various (fragile and conflict affected) contexts, including Sudan and South Sudan, Somalia, India, South Africa, Bahrain, Zimbabwe and Papua New Guinea. The work I did ranged from coordinating and managing hospitals, clinics and therapeutic feeding centers, to organizing mass vaccination campaigns and responding to cholera outbreaks. 

In Zimbabwe, South Africa and Papua New Guinea, the focus of my work was to establish and run community based interventions, responding to the medical and psychosocial needs of survivors of Sexual and Gender Based Violence. I have been involved in qualitative and quantitative research.
Since May 2017 I work at KIT Royal Tropical Institute, mainly in the areas of Sexual and Reproductive Health and Rights (SRHR)  and fragile settings and am engaged in the following projects:
- Conducting research on Sexual Violence in Humanitarian settings (Haiti, Yemen, Nigeria)
- Conducting a narrative review on Sexual and Reproductive Health and Rights for people affected by conflict, fragility and crisis (in preparation of a Share-Net International Co-creation conference)
- Development and implementation of a tailor made training on SRHR, Human Rights Based Approach, Gender and Health Systems Strengthening, for health care professionals and managers working in Yemen.
- Teaching at the Masters in Public Health and various short courses and student advise (thesis) and tutoring
